@startuml push-flow
title `dolt push` through a GitHub URL

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam monochrome false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #0969DA
    LifeLineBorderColor #0969DA
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #EAF3FF
    ParticipantBorderColor #0969DA
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #EAF3FF
    ActorBorderColor #0969DA
    ActorBackgroundColor #D9EDFF
}

actor "you" as USER
participant "dolt" as DOLT
participant "git credential\nhelper" as CRED
participant "github.com\n(Smart HTTP)" as GH
database "refs/dolt/data\n(on GitHub)" as REF

USER -> DOLT : dolt remote add origin\n  https://github.com/.../repo.git
note right of DOLT : URL ends in .git →\n  auto-prefix with git+
USER -> DOLT : dolt push -u origin main
DOLT -> CRED : ask for credentials\n(same helper git uses)
CRED --> DOLT : token
DOLT -> GH : git send-pack (Smart HTTP)\nwith refs/dolt/data and refs/heads/main
GH -> REF : store chunks as git blobs\non refs/dolt/data
GH --> DOLT : ok (new branch, new ref)
DOLT --> USER : "* [new branch] main -> main"

@enduml
